questions.question_text_1: Which of the following statement(s) is/are true about Breadth First Search (BFS) on an undirected graph?
question_texts: Which of the following statement(s) is/are true about Breadth First Search (BFS) on an undirected graph?

options.option_text: BFS systematically computes reachability in graphs.
The Time complexity of BFS is O(mn) when Adjacency List is used and O(m2)when Adjacency Matrix is used, where m represents the number of vertices and n represents thenumber of edges.
BFS cannot be used to check for cycles in the graph.
Paths discovered by BFS are the shortest paths in terms of the number ofedges from source to destination.

questions.question_text_1: A university offers an online learning program in which there are 11 courses in total. The program is divided into semesters of 6 months. Students can take any number of courses in one semester, but they can take a course only if they have finished taking its prerequisites.
questions.question_text_2: A university offers an online learning program in which there are 11 courses in total. The program is divided into semesters of 6 months. Students can take any number of courses in one semester, but they can take a course only if they have finished taking its prerequisites.    There is no constraint on how many courses a student can take in a semester. The minimum number of semesters required to complete all 11 courses is ___.  NOTE: Enter your answer to the nearest integer.
